<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas or words in your writing, include the author&#8217;s name and any relevant page number(s), in parentheses, immediately following the cited material. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Smith A5).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the author of the work in your sentence, with the relevant page number(s) in parentheses (if necessary).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith suggests that &#34;the default position is markedly affected&#34; (A5).
</blockquote>
